WEBVTT

00:02.546 --> 00:04.846
OV! OV! OV! OV!

00:04.848 --> 00:07.115
OV! OV! OV!

00:07.117 --> 00:10.584
OV! OV! OV! OV!

00:10.586 --> 00:11.752
OV! OV...

00:11.754 --> 00:12.920
Yo, yo, yo.

00:12.922 --> 00:14.555
Thank you very much.

00:14.557 --> 00:15.523
Let me tell you a story.

00:15.525 --> 00:17.892
When Osvaldo V.
first told me

00:17.894 --> 00:21.194
that he wanted to support
the youth center here,

00:21.196 --> 00:22.830
I wasn't surprised.

00:22.832 --> 00:24.632
He's not just
a superstar,

00:24.634 --> 00:28.234
he's the homie that never
forgot where he came from.

00:30.872 --> 00:34.774
So I want you all
to welcome home OV.

00:36.878 --> 00:38.812
We love you, OV.

00:38.814 --> 00:41.414
Thank you, Gerry.
Guerrero,

00:41.416 --> 00:44.950
my friend, my lawyer.
Let me just say

00:44.952 --> 00:47.152
I'm glad to be back,
because I owe the barrio.

00:47.154 --> 00:49.555
And this youth center.

00:49.557 --> 00:52.724
The people that work there--
they didn't just save my life.

00:52.726 --> 00:53.992
They gave me a future.

00:53.994 --> 00:56.361
The least I can do is try to give

00:56.363 --> 00:57.563
somebody else
the same opportunity,

00:57.565 --> 00:59.230
you know what I mean?
You got to give back.

00:59.232 --> 01:00.998
And he certainly did.

01:01.000 --> 01:03.000
He put his money
where his mouth is,

01:03.002 --> 01:06.170
to the tune of 100K.

01:06.840 --> 01:08.539
So say hello

01:08.541 --> 01:10.808
to my little friend OV!

01:12.345 --> 01:13.978
OV! OV!

01:13.980 --> 01:15.713
OV! OV!
OV!

01:15.715 --> 01:19.516
OV! OV! OV!

01:27.893 --> 01:30.259
You the one that called in

01:30.261 --> 01:31.761
somebody trying to
break into my house?

01:31.763 --> 01:33.196
We don't know what we got.

01:33.198 --> 01:35.698
Neighborhood watch spotted this
guy looking in your windows.

01:35.700 --> 01:36.832
He says he's your

01:36.834 --> 01:39.468
brother-in-law?
Jimmy?

01:39.470 --> 01:41.022
Hey, yo, Danny.

01:41.563 --> 01:43.046
What the hell are
you doing here?

01:43.207 --> 01:44.807
I told these guys I was your
best friend in high school.

01:44.809 --> 01:46.375
I introduced you to your wife.
Sir...

01:46.377 --> 01:47.409
It's fine,
it's fine.

01:47.411 --> 01:48.978
I got it from here.
Thank you.

01:48.980 --> 01:50.545
Hey, I'm-I'm sorry, Danny,
I'm sorry.

01:50.547 --> 01:51.946
It's...
these guys, man...

01:51.948 --> 01:53.347
I haven't seen your
face in two years,

01:53.349 --> 01:55.416
you show up at my house
unannounced, poking around?

01:55.418 --> 01:58.520
Yeah, well... it was kind of
a spur of the moment thing.

01:58.522 --> 02:01.188
Uh-huh.
Come on, cut to the chase.

02:01.190 --> 02:02.724
What are you doing here?

02:03.994 --> 02:05.226
This girl I've been seeing--

02:05.228 --> 02:07.028
her, her husband
got the wrong idea.

02:07.030 --> 02:08.829
Meaning he got the right idea.

02:08.830 --> 02:11.464
I just need to lay low
for a few days, and...

02:11.466 --> 02:13.466
Oh, wait a minute.

02:13.468 --> 02:15.468
Come on, Danny, we're family.

02:15.470 --> 02:18.471
You remember Owl's Head Park?
The Kay brothers

02:18.473 --> 02:21.207
were gonna kick your punk ass.
I was there for you.

02:21.209 --> 02:22.809
You mean Larry and his crew?
Yeah. Look, you can't

02:22.811 --> 02:24.377
keep handing me that bill,
Jimmy, all right?

02:24.379 --> 02:25.912
I paid it a long time ago.

02:27.448 --> 02:29.015
Come on, Danny.

02:29.017 --> 02:31.483
Can you help me out
for old time's sake?

02:31.485 --> 02:34.253
And I'd love to see
Linda and the boys.

02:36.290 --> 02:38.591
Oh...

02:38.593 --> 02:41.360
All right, fine. You can stay
for a day or two, all right?

02:41.362 --> 02:42.694
And don't make me regret it.

02:42.696 --> 02:44.829
Danny, you're a saint.
I knew I could count on you.

02:44.831 --> 02:46.798
Ah, no hugs! Don't hug.

02:46.800 --> 02:49.701
Come on...

02:49.703 --> 02:51.269
Bro, it's so good to see you.

02:51.271 --> 02:52.537
Oh, man, it's been a long time.

02:52.539 --> 02:54.739
I flipped out when I saw you
out in that crowd, man.

02:54.741 --> 02:57.576
I can't believe you came back
with that fat check, man.

02:57.578 --> 02:59.577
Yo, man, I got to be
true to the game, right?

02:59.579 --> 03:02.412
I mean, and, honestly, yo, it's
my pleasure to be lucky enough

03:02.414 --> 03:04.314
to have something to
give back, you know-- oh!

03:04.316 --> 03:06.550
NYPD!
Come on, man!

03:06.552 --> 03:08.118
You're under arrest!
What-what'd I do, man?

03:08.120 --> 03:10.554
- Police! What are you talking about, man?
- Leave him alone!

03:10.556 --> 03:12.990
- You're under arrest! Hands together!
- What are you doing?!

03:12.992 --> 03:14.625
You better listen to me.
I'm a cop.

03:14.627 --> 03:15.959
Come on, Ger-Gerry!

03:15.961 --> 03:16.993
That's my client!

03:16.995 --> 03:18.761
You're in a lot of trouble,
Officer!

03:18.763 --> 03:20.129
He's under arrest.
Yes, you are!

03:22.300 --> 03:24.067
Did you even look
at the crime scene video?

03:24.069 --> 03:25.234
Yeah, I looked at it.
It was

03:25.236 --> 03:26.636
the wrong guy.
Who, from 20 yards,

03:26.638 --> 03:27.804
looked like
the right guy.

03:27.806 --> 03:29.405
Honest mistake.
You're missing the point.

03:29.407 --> 03:30.640
That <i>is</i> the point.

03:30.642 --> 03:32.341
Nobody's perfect.
We'll apologize.

03:32.343 --> 03:33.775
Did I hear “apologize”?
Yeah.

03:33.777 --> 03:35.577
We made a mistake,
we'll apologize for it.

03:35.579 --> 03:36.979
Too late, Guerrero
has already filed

03:36.981 --> 03:38.714
to see the outcome
of any previous

03:38.716 --> 03:41.883
disciplinary hearings
against Sergeant Donahue.

03:42.786 --> 03:44.219
Were there any?

03:44.221 --> 03:45.754
He's had a few complaints.

03:45.756 --> 03:47.155
Same as any other active cop.

03:47.157 --> 03:49.324
Any substantiated?
At least three.

03:49.326 --> 03:51.425
I'm not sure how serious
any of them were,

03:51.427 --> 03:52.627
but we're looking into 'em now.

03:52.629 --> 03:53.995
Let's assume
they're not dynamite.

03:53.997 --> 03:56.330
We share them with Guerrero,
this thing deflates.

03:56.332 --> 03:57.531
We can't
share them.

03:57.533 --> 03:58.666
Legal says we cannot release

03:58.668 --> 04:00.701
those records.
It is now a state law.

04:00.703 --> 04:02.103
There's got to be
a way around it.

04:02.105 --> 04:03.137
We're not gonna share 'em.

04:03.139 --> 04:04.772
It would alienate
the rank and file.

04:04.774 --> 04:06.773
And lawyers like Guerrero
are gonna try to turn every

04:06.775 --> 04:08.241
mole hill into a mountain.
But if we don't

04:08.243 --> 04:10.110
release 'em, it looks
like we're hiding something.

04:10.112 --> 04:13.980
Hey! Could we just
find out what we have?

04:13.982 --> 04:15.281
Yes, sir.

